com.avaya.cmapi.callinformation

Class CallInformationAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.avaya.cmapi.callinformation.CallInformationAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CallInformationListener, java.util.EventListener

    public class CallInformationAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
implements CallInformationListener
    Implements a "do nothing" callback method for each call information event type. To learn more about how to use a listener adapter, see Using Listeners in the Device, Media & Call Control (DMCC) API.

      • linkUp

        public void linkUp(LinkUpEvent upEvent)
        Description copied from interface: CallInformationListener
        Called when the call information link becomes operational. Occurs the first time the link is brought up, as well as every time the link is brought up after being down.

        Specified by:
        linkUp in interface CallInformationListener
        Parameters:

      • linkDown

        public void linkDown(LinkDownEvent downEvent)
        Description copied from interface: CallInformationListener
        Called when the call information link becomes inoperational. Occurs when it is determined that Communication Manager is not responding or Communication Manager and Communication Manager API are out of synch. Response will indicate which link is down and whether the connector server will attempt to reconnect automatically.

        Specified by:
        linkDown in interface CallInformationListener
        Parameters:
        downEvent - information about the name of the link, and whether attempts will be made to reconnect automatically
